cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.SE 

The paper presents a framework for training deep neural surrogates of stochastic simulators, which involves techniques from machine learning (such as deep learning and probabilistic programming) and systems engineering (such as simulator modeling and approximation). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper also involves techniques from neural networks (cs.NE) and software engineering (cs.SE), which are less prominent but still relevant sub-categories.
